Class
Description
BadIsbn10Exception
This exception class is used to indicate that an invalid ISBN-10 has been encountered.
BadIsbn13Exception
This exception class is used to indicate that an invalid ISBN-13 has been encountered.
BadIsbnLengthException
This exception class is used to indicate that an invalid ISBN length has been encountered.
BadPriceException
This exception class is used to indicate that an invalid price has been encountered.
BadYearException
This exception class is used to indicate that an invalid year has been encountered.
Book
This class represents a book, which includes a title, author(s), price, International Standard Book Number (ISBN), genre, and publication year.
BookCollection
This class represents a collection of books.
Driver
This class represents a driver for running the different parts of the assignment.
MissingFieldException
This exception class is used to indicate that a required field is missing.
Part1
Part1 reads input file names from "Part1_input_file_names.txt", creates 8 output files based on book genre and parses each input file.
Part2
Part2 checks the input files for the semantic errors and then serializes the valid records in binary files
Part3
This class provides functionality for viewing and selecting book data from a list of serialized book arrays.
StingFieldsBook
StingFieldsBook represents a book object with all fields as strings
TooFewFieldsException
This exception is thrown when there are too few fields in a record.
TooManyFieldsException
This exception is thrown when there are too many fields in a record.
UnknownGenreException
This exception is thrown when the genre of the record is unknown.
